{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "web:psalms.62",
    "translationId": "web",
    "bookSlug": "psalms",
    "chapterNumber": 62,
    "referenceLabel": "Psalms 62",
    "summary": "Source text for Psalms 62 in World English Bible."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.62.1",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 62,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 62:1",
      "text": "My soul rests in God alone. My salvation is from him.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.62.2",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 62,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 62:2",
      "text": "He alone is my rock, my salvation, and my fortress. I will never be greatly shaken.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.62.3",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 62,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 62:3",
      "text": "How long will you assault a man? Would all of you throw him down, like a leaning wall, like a tottering fence?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.62.4",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 62,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 62:4",
      "text": "They fully intend to throw him down from his lofty place. They delight in lies. They bless with their mouth, but they curse inwardly. Selah.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.62.5",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 62,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 62:5",
      "text": "My soul, wait in silence for God alone, for my expectation is from him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.62.6",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 62,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 62:6",
      "text": "He alone is my rock and my salvation, my fortress. I will not be shaken.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.62.7",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 62,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 62:7",
      "text": "My salvation and my honor is with God. The rock of my strength, and my refuge, is in God.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.62.8",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 62,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 62:8",
      "text": "Trust in him at all times, you people. Pour out your heart before him. God is a refuge for us. Selah.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.62.9",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 62,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 62:9",
      "text": "Surely men of low degree are just a breath, and men of high degree are a lie. In the balances they will go up. They are together lighter than a breath.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.62.10",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 62,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 62:10",
      "text": "Don’t trust in oppression. Don’t become vain in robbery. If riches increase, don’t set your heart on them.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.62.11",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 62,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 62:11",
      "text": "God has spoken once; twice I have heard this, that power belongs to God.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:psalms.62.12",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "psalms",
      "chapterNumber": 62,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Psalms 62:12",
      "text": "Also to you, Lord, belongs loving kindness, for you reward every man according to his work.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
